Beginner's Guide to Playing Online Slots

Jamieson

If you've never played slots at an online casino, our beginner's guide covers everything you need to know to start playing and winning online. Our newbie guide makes it easy to get started and we cover information about playing slots as well as advice on opening a casino account. Casino software type Banking options and more


Choosing an Online Casino

There are many factors to consider when choosing to play at an online casino. Obviously you want a casino with a wide variety of slots. But other factors should also be considered. Payout percentage software type Comp and bonuses and your country of residence. At All Online Slots we cover a lot of information about online casinos so You can easily find the casino that is right for you here.


Easy tips for new players

Once you have chosen an online casino we recommend doing the following to ensure you are fully informed and ready before you start playing.


Always read the casino terms and conditions before you play

Always read the bonus terms and conditions before you claim the bonus.


Download and installation

If you choose a download-based casino, you will need to download and install the software before you can play. This is a simple process. Click the download button on the casino website to download the software. Once downloaded, double click the installer icon and follow the instructions.


Account Registration

Once you have the software on your computer, you can register an account. When you open a casino you will be prompted to register. Here you have to enter your details including name and address. It is essential that you enter the correct details as these will be used to send your winnings. Filling in any false details will result in your account being closed.


Deposit And Withdrawal

To play for real money, you will need to deposit money into your casino account. To do this, you need to go to the bank or cashier section of the casino. Here you will be able to select all deposit methods and the amount to be deposited.The cashier's section is also where you withdraw funds from your account. Select the Withdraw button, then you can choose the amount to withdraw and the method. In most cases, your withdrawal method will be the same as the method you used to deposit. Other payment options often include checks and bank transfers.


Security And Authentication

As part of the security measures used by online casinos, you will need to verify your identity. This includes emailing or faxing a copy of your photo ID. The most recent utility bill showing your address and, if you're using a credit card, must be photographed on the front and back of the card. You should also cover the middle eight on the card and the CVV number in the image you send to the casino. This is enough to verify the card without having to email the full image of the card.


Asking For Help

All the casinos that we have listed in All Online Slots have many support options. If you have questions, you can email the casino or in most cases call or chat online via live chat. You'll also find numerous help sections within most online casino software so you can quickly find answers to your questions.
